{"id":88687,"title":"Managing patients with cervical spine injury.","abstract":"Common measures to establish spinal immobilisation at the scene of an accident include keeping the patient's head still, applying a rigid cervical collar and transporting the patient on a rigid spinal board to an emergency department. This article reviews the literature about spinal immobilisation practices in emergency settings, including best-practice guidance and papers on immobilisation, imaging, rapport with patients and complications. ","date":"2014-05-08","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24806864","annotations":[{"name":"Cervical collar","weight":0.894932,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_collar"},{"name":"Cervical vertebrae","weight":0.811212,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_vertebrae"},{"name":"Vertebral column","weight":0.799476,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebral_column"},{"name":"Long spine board","weight":0.789375,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_spine_board"},{"name":"Emergency department","weight":0.785202,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency_department"},{"name":"Injury","weight":0.738937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injury"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.733831,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Spinal cord injury","weight":0.688906,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spinal_cord_injury"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.626967,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Accident","weight":0.382358,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accident"},{"name":"Medical imaging","weight":0.369578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging"},{"name":"Emergency","weight":0.322407,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency"},{"name":"